author: Felicia Schwartz
title: U.S., Pakistan Discuss Nuclear Weapons Program
text:
WASHINGTON—The U.S. and Pakistan are discussing ways to limit Pakistan’s growing nuclear weapons program, people familiar with the discussions said, in talks that are under way as the country’s prime minister plans a visit to Washington next week.
However, the exploratory talks aren’t considered likely to progress very far, officials said, because Pakistan is seen as unwilling to accept limitations on its nuclear program.
